  "overall_supervision_plan": "Newly identified risks will be recorded and mitigated accordingly and risk acceptance will be approved at the appropriate level. Leadership to include Troop Chain of Command, Range Officer in Charge, SUAS Master Trainer. Vehicle crew members will be the primary implementors of safety measures during movement. The OIC and SUAS Master Trainer will give all Soldiers a range safety brief and are responsible for overseeing safety during the entirety of training. Medics will be on site at all times and postured to respond to injuries and to evacuate casualties. Medics and MEV will conduct AXP route recon and response rehearsal prior to range start.",
